[{'action': 'opened', 'author': 'fhemberger', 'comment_id': None, 'datetime': '2017-07-28 13:55:19+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': "It's been a long time since we last added new contributors to the project.

It's a bit of manual labor, since I use a customized script to determine all new committers since a given date which are not already project contributors. Then we need someone with admin rights on GitHub to add those people to the website team. This has been done by @mikeal in the past, we need to find someone who is willing to take over â€¦", 'title': 'Add new contributors (July 2017)', 'type': 'issue'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'phillipj', 'comment_id': 318759909.0, 'datetime': '2017-07-28 20:56:11+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': 'Finding new contributors could possibly be done by adding functionality to the https://github.com/nodejs/github-bot if someone feels for a challenge.

As for adding people into the nodejs organisation, there has been a somewhat controversial discussion using a bot for that as well. Maybe @username_3 has some updates around that, as he has given that a shot more than once..', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'sotayamashita', 'comment_id': 318803326.0, 'datetime': '2017-07-29 04:32:30+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_2', 'text': '@username_0 Wii you write code for nodejs-github-bot to add collaborators?', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'williamkapke', 'comment_id': 318936813.0, 'datetime': '2017-07-30 23:13:09+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_3', 'text': "The latest discussion on using a bot to do it was here: https://github.com/nodejs/community-committee/issues/22

Any member of the CTC or TSC is empowered to add people you ask them to. In fact, that is one of their specific duties. It would be good to have some of those folks getting familiar with doing it.
So- as soon as ya'll decide who is a new collaborator- just ping those groups and ask for someone to volunteer to invite them to the org and add them to the `Website` and `Members` team. (it's pretty easy)

Of course- ping me again if you don't get a volunteer in a reasonable time and I'll escalate it
<sup>(I really doubt that'll be needed- I'm just making sure you know you'll never be stuck on this!)</sup>", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
